import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
# Now let us look at the correlation coefficient of each of these variables #
x_cols = [col for col in data.columns if col not in ['mcd_global_lcat_id_nu','yoy_sales_chg','MISCELLANEOS_iTEMS','SPECIAL','SERVICES','PROMOTIONAL','HM_SIDE_ITEMS','BEVERAGE_MLTIPLES','mid_tier','core_price_tier']]

labels = []
values = []
for col in x_cols:
    labels.append(col)
    values.append(np.corrcoef(data[col].values, data.yoy_sales_chg.values)[0,1])
    
ind = np.arange(len(labels))
width = 0.2
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6,12))
rects = ax.barh(ind, np.array(values), color='y')
ax.set_yticks(ind+((width)/2.))
ax.set_yticklabels(labels, rotation='horizontal')
ax.set_xlabel("Correlation coefficient")
ax.set_title("Correlation coefficient")

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn import preprocessing

import time
from time import time
import datetime

from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor, GradientBoostingRegressor, BaggingRegressor
from sklearn.linear_model import RidgeCV,ElasticNetCV,BayesianRidge
from sklearn.model_selection import KFold, GridSearchCV, RandomizedSearchCV
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler,scale, PolynomialFeatures,FunctionTransformer
from sklearn.metrics import make_scorer, mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error, r2_score
from scipy.stats import randint as sp_randint

def mape(y_true, y_pred): 
    return np.mean(np.abs((y_true - y_pred) / y_true)) * 100

def rms(y_true, y_pred):
    return np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred))
rmse  = make_scorer(rms, greater_is_better=False)
